                },
                {
                    "self": "http:\/\/framework.zend.com\/issues\/rest\/api\/latest\/comment\/12384",
                    "author": {
                        "self": "http:\/\/framework.zend.com\/issues\/rest\/api\/latest\/user?username=matthew",
                        "name": "matthew",
                        "displayName": "Matthew Weier O'Phinney",
                        "active": true
                    },
                    "body": "This has been done for the router and dispatcher in revision 3004; should it also be done for the action controllers?",
                    "updateAuthor": {
                        "self": "http:\/\/framework.zend.com\/issues\/rest\/api\/latest\/user?username=matthew",
                        "name": "matthew",
                        "displayName": "Matthew Weier O'Phinney",
                        "active": true
                    },
                    "created": "2007-01-25T16:23:50.000+0000",
                    "updated": "2007-01-25T16:23:50.000+0000"
                },
                {
                    "self": "http:\/\/framework.zend.com\/issues\/rest\/api\/latest\/comment\/12438",
                    "author": {
                        "self": "http:\/\/framework.zend.com\/issues\/rest\/api\/latest\/user?username=matthew",
                        "name": "matthew",
                        "displayName": "Matthew Weier O'Phinney",
                        "active": true
                    },
                    "body": "In discussion with Martel, will also add to response object, plugin broker and plugins, and action controller.",
                    "updateAuthor": {
                        "self": "http:\/\/framework.zend.com\/issues\/rest\/api\/latest\/user?username=matthew",
                        "name": "matthew",
                        "displayName": "Matthew Weier O'Phinney",
                        "active": true
                    },
                    "created": "2007-01-29T15:13:34.000+0000",
                    "updated": "2007-01-29T15:13:34.000+0000"
                },
                {
                    "self": "http:\/\/framework.zend.com\/issues\/rest\/api\/latest\/comment\/12585",
                    "author": {
                        "self": "http:\/\/framework.zend.com\/issues\/rest\/api\/latest\/user?username=matthew",
                        "name": "matthew",
                        "displayName": "Matthew Weier O'Phinney",
                        "active": true
                    },
                    "body": "Zend_Controller_Front is a singleton class, and, as such, is accessible from any other piece of code via Zend_Controller_Front::getInstance().\n\nFurthermore, because the $_instance property storing the singleton instance is protected, by overriding the getInstance() method, you can effectively extend the class and still maintain access to the singleton via Zend_Controller_Front::getInstance().\n\nAs an example:\n\n{code}\nclass My_Front_Controller extends Zend_Controller_Front\n{\n    public function getInstance()\n    {\n        if (null === self::$_instance) {\n            self::$_instance = new self();\n        }\n\n        return self::$_instance;\n    }\n}\n\n$front = My_Controller_Front::getInstance();\necho get_class($front); \/\/ 'My_Controller_Front'\n\n\/\/ later...\n$front = Zend_Controller_Front::getInstance();\necho get_class($front); \/\/ 'My_Controller_Front'\n{code}\n\nOne might argue that static methods do not perform as well as object methods; however, the number of calls to retrieve a front controller instance are likely to be very few, and thus would have little impact on performance.\n\nFinally, if desired, one can simply push the front controller instance into the\nchain via setParam(): \n\n{code}\n$front->setParam('front', $this).\n{code}\n",
                    "updateAuthor": {
                        "self": "http:\/\/framework.zend.com\/issues\/rest\/api\/latest\/user?username=matthew",
                        "name": "matthew",
                        "displayName": "Matthew Weier O'Phinney",
                        "active": true
                    },
                    "created": "2007-02-08T08:56:26.000+0000",
                    "updated": "2007-02-08T08:56:26.000+0000"
                }
            ]
        }
